---
description: core-be public API contract — route params, public ids, status policy, headers
globs:
  - "src/domains/**/*.routes.ts"
  - "src/domains/**/*.dto.ts"
  - "src/domains/**/*.controller.ts"
  - "tooling/openapi/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Path params: snake_case + semantic (`{plan_id}`, `{subscription_id}`, never `{id}`), registered in PARAM_NAME_TO_ENTITY; Zod params keys identical to the param name. The active organization is carried by the signed `org` JWT claim — routes do NOT take an `{organization_id}` path segment; the active-org resource is singular `/tenancy/organization` (sub-resources nest under it).
- Public ids: `<prefix>_<21 [a-z0-9]>` via generatePublicId(entity); external field name is always `id`; never write "public id" in docs.
- Status policy (middleware-enforced): GET 200, POST 201, PUT/PATCH 200, DELETE 204; webhooks + MCP stay 200. Update route-success-statuses.json with any route change.
- Error codes (full guide docs/reference/api/response-codes.md): 400 malformed shape only — every POST/PATCH/PUT has it; omit only on param-less query-less GET/DELETE; 401 token problems (recovery hint in message); 403 permission; 404 not-exists incl. cross-org; 409 state conflict (mutating); 422 business rule / idempotency payload mismatch / capability-not-available-for-resource-type (mutating); 413/415 body size/content-type (POST/PATCH/PUT); 429 everywhere with Retry-After + X-RateLimit-*; 500 never intentional. Never invent statuses outside this list.
- Personal vs team org (one surface): both types share /tenancy/organization/*; a PERSONAL org rejects the 5 team-only mutations (invite/add member, custom roles, transfer-ownership, delete org) with 422 (UnprocessableEntityError, immutable type) — keyed in TEAM_ONLY_ROUTE_KEYS; the org response carries a type-derived `capabilities` object. Authenticated self-service routes live under /auth/me/* (MFA, passkey register); login-flow stays public off /me. Invitation kill = revoke (DELETE …/invitations/:invitation_id). Every route needs schema {summary,description,tags} — gated by validate:route-schema-docs.
- Headers: Authorization Bearer (security scheme), X-Organization-Id, Idempotency-Key (required on the 8 idempotencyRequired writes), X-Captcha-Token (public auth forms), X-CSRF-Token (refresh only), Stripe-Signature (Stripe-sent). All custom headers use X- forms; standards keep fixed names (Authorization, Idempotency-Key, Stripe-Signature); ecosystem X- standards unchanged (X-Request-Id, X-Api-Key, X-CSRF-Token, X-RateLimit-*, X-Forwarded-For).
- After any change: routes:catalog → docs:generate:multilang → docs:postman → docs:check + route-status gates.
